    fix(frontend): close demo-login bypass and remove client-side loan-limit math
    
    Prototype-logic audit fixes (owner session, all frontend gates pass —
    typecheck, ESLint, Vitest 137/137, build):
    
    - MP00_Login: remove the ungated onLogin demo fallback; onSubmitLogin
      (real portal session API) is now required; empty credentials show a
      validation error instead of any login path.
    - App: drop the unconditional handleDemoLogin('borrower') wiring; all
      demo paths now sit behind DEMO_AUTH_ENABLED; logout clears the user.
    - RoleContext: boot as exported UNAUTHENTICATED_USER (no identity,
      roles, or permissions) instead of a staff fixture; add clearUser().
    - MP05_NewApplication: remove client-computed loan limits (wrong
      formula, hard-coded land limit 675000, local Math.min submission
      gate); limits are server-determined during credit assessment (006Z2
      owns the borrower-scoped projection endpoint).
    - Regression tests for all of the above (7 new tests).
    
    Recorded in docs/slices/005FA2 (Complete) and 006Z2 (interim note).
    
